In a Single Page Application (SPA), elements are often loaded dynamically as the user interacts with the page. If you try to scroll before the elements are loaded, you might not get the expected results.

One common approach to force an SPA to scroll down is to use a loop that repeatedly attempts to scroll to the bottom of the page until a condition is met. This could be a certain element appearing, a certain number of elements being loaded, or the scroll position not changing between iterations.

